The maximum number of iterations or tests possible is p / m. Let's call it T. Also let the minmum number of pigs needed be x.
Each pig can be used to represent (T + 1) states - it does not die, it dies after first test, dies after second test,.... , it dies after Tth test.
Using each of these states to represent a bucket, we get the equation (T + 1) ^ x >= n

